Character.isDigit(c)	        // checks if c is 0–9
Character.isLetter(c)	        // checks if c is A–Z or a–z
Character.isLetterOrDigit(c)	// alphanumeric check
Character.isLowerCase(c)	    // checks lowercase
Character.isUpperCase(c)	    // checks uppercase
Character.isWhitespace(c)	    // space, tab, newline

Character.toLowerCase(c)	    // convert to lowercase (Not inplace, but returns)
Character.toUpperCase(c)	    // convert to uppercase (Not inplace, but returns)

**String Methods That Deal with Characters**
s.charAt(i)	                  // get char at index
s.toCharArray()	              // convert string → char[]

s.indexOf(c)	                //first occurrence
s.lastIndexOf(c)	            //last occurrence
s.contains(...)	              //string contains char/substring

-char array → String
String s = new String(arr);

-Convert char digit to integer
int x = c - '0'
